ckground. If you want to receive location updates while running in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"background, you must use the Core Location framework."}]}]}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNUserTrackingMode/MLNUserTrackingModeFollowWithHeading":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnusertrackingmode\/mlnusertrackingmodefollowwithheading","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The map follows the user location and rotates when the heading changes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default user location annotation displays a fan-shaped indicator with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the current heading. The heading indicator represents the direction the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device is facing, which is sized according to the reported accuracy."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNUserTrackingMode\/MLNUserTrackingModeFollowWithHeading","role":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"MLNUserTrackingModeFollowWithHeading","fragments":[{"text":"MLNUserTrackingModeFollowWithHeading","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNUserLocation":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnuserlocation","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNUserLocation"}],"type":"topic","title":"MLNUserLocation","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNUserLocation","abstract":[{"text":"The MLNUserLocation class defines a specific type of annotation that identifies","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the user’s current location. You do not create instances of this class","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"directly. Instead, you retrieve an existing ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNUserLocation","type":"reference"},{"text":" object from the","type":"text"},{"text":